    <div class="splashPanel__main" role="region" aria-label="Splash panel">
      <h2 class="splashPanel__title" id="when-will-mortgage-rates-rise-or-fall">When will mortgage rates rise or fall?</h2>
      <div class="rich-text-container" role="region" aria-label="Rich text undefined">
        <p class="richTextElement">UK mortgage rates tend to increase or decrease with changes to the <a href="#">Bank of England base rate</a>.</p>
        <p class="richTextElement">If the base rate increases, so do mortgage rates. If the bank rate decreases, mortgage rates go down.</p>
        <p class="richTextElement">There was a meeting of the Bank of England Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) in January 2020. In the meeting, 7 out of 9 committee members voted to keep the base rate at 0.75%.</p>
        <p class="richTextElement">This suggests that the MPC may vote to change the base rate later this year. But it's difficult to predict when it could happen.</p>
        <p class="richTextElement">The MPC meets roughly every 6 weeks. There were also meetings on 26 March and the 7 May 2020. </p>
        <p class="richTextElement">The decision to change the base rate depends on the UK economy up to and after we leave the European Union at the end of 2020.</p>
      </div>
